menu "Hisense A/C firmware"

config HISENSE_DEBUG_BUILD
    bool "Debug flavour (diagnostic console + verbose bring-up logging)"
    default n
    help
        Build the DEBUG flavour of this firmware.

        When set, the image includes the :2323 diagnostic console (features / poll /
        watch / decode / selftest / token) and the verbose bring-up logging. That
        console is a bench instrument: it has NO authentication and can drive the
        A/C bus, so it must not ship on a deployed appliance controller.

        Leave this OFF (the default) for release images. Build the debug flavour with
        an explicit profile instead:

            idf.py -DSDKCONFIG_DEFAULTS="sdkconfig.defaults;sdkconfig.debug" build

        Only logging, the console and diagnostics may differ between the two
        flavours. Anything that changes bus or Matter behaviour would make bench
        results meaningless for the shipped image.

endmenu
